AD“Talks with China are going very well,” Trump told reporters Tuesday, although he didn’t offer specifics.
He said that because the United States imports more goods from China than it exports, it creates an unfair imbalance that must be remedied.
Trump and other White House officials have said they are making progress, particularly in areas related to currency ma­nipu­la­tion and intellectual property theft.
But they have not released specifics about the pact, making it hard to judge the scope of any deal.
ADWhite House officials have said the deal would not need congressional approval.